projects.name: Go-Volunteer
projects.description: Developed a volunteer recruitment platform facilitating communication between volunteers and organizations. Implemented MongoDB as the primary database for storing user details, enabling authentication, job posting, and job application functionalities. Designed and built the frontend using React.js, ensuring a responsive and user-friendly interface. Developed the backend using Express.js, providing robust API endpoints for seamless communication between the frontend and the database.

projects.name: Steganography Application
projects.description: Developed a Steganography tool integrating React.js for the frontend and Flask for the backend. Implemented encryption and decryption functionalities to embed and extract messages securely within images. Stored the secret key within the image pixels for transmission and retrieval at the receivers end, ensuring secure communication.

projects.name: Decentralized Token Exchanger
projects.description: Developed a Decentralized Token Exchanger allowing users to exchange native tokens with faucet tokens. Utilized smart contracts for core functionalities such as adding, removing liquidity, and swapping tokens. Deployed the application on ThirdWeb for enhanced integration and decentralized operations.

experiences.description: Conducted external penetration testing as an intern at Cestro Technologies for three months. Developed skills in vulnerability assessment, penetration testing, and security analysis. Utilized tools such as Burp Suite for comprehensive evaluations of web applications and networks. Detected and mitigated security threats to enhance cybersecurity protocols. Produced detailed reports outlining findings and recommendations in the format of security Assessment Report.
